WorldStage Newsonline– The stock price of Nigerian Breweries Plc (NB) gained 1.5% on Wednesday from N42 to N43.5 per share during trading at the Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE) as the company’s foreign core investor, Heineken Brouwerijen B.V remained active in the buying market. The leading brewing company in Nigeria on Wednesday confirmed fresh share dealing by insiders involving Heineken that purchased 04,935 units at N41.04  per unit which amounted to N8,410,532.4. In a notification signed by Uaboi G. Agbebaku, Company Secretary released by the Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE), Heineken Brouwerijen B.V transaction took place on 1st, 10th, 18th & 21st September, 2020. WorldStage earlier reported that Heineken Brouwerijen B.V purchased 144,965 units at N34.21 per unit which amounted to N4,959,252.65 on 10th & 26th August, 2020. NB stock witnessed active trading on the NSE on Wednesday with 49 transactions involving            6,171,622 shares valued at  N266,949,685.2542 . Nigerian Breweries Plc, is the pioneer and largest brewing company in Nigeria. It serves the Nigerian market and exports to other parts of West Africa.